% (version nr. see below) %% DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE
% TeX hyphenation patterns for the Hungarian language come in two versions,
% since the official orthographical rules (MHSz \S 231 and 238) allow 
% hyphenation of composita either according to their constituents
% (this is implemented in hyphen.tex) or according to the simple
% phonematic rules (MHSz \S 224, implemented by huhyph-phonet.tex).
%
% primary ftp site  ftp://clphx.btk.ppke.hu/pub/tex/
%   available from CTAN: languages/hyphenation/
%
% Versions 1.0 to 2.1 have been manually created by MIKLÓS Dezs\H{o}, 1989.
% Further manual changes by MAYER Gyula, 1991--98.

% Nov 4, 1998 make catcodes local
%		(thanks to Thomas Esser <te@informatik.uni-hannover.de>)

% Version 4.x is automatically generated from a dictionary
% file by Mayer Gyula, 2002.
% This project has been sponsored by the IKB, http://www.ikb.hu/
% (Informatikai Kormánybiztosság, Budapest, a Hungarian government agency)
% (whose name has changed since then)
% under grant nr. SZT-IS-10/3 and by
% TypoTeX Ltd., Budapest, http://www.typotex.hu/

%   Thanks to both of them
%   for the licence to freely distribute
%   these Hungarian hyphenation patterns for TeX.
%
% Please send corrections to Mayer Gyula, gam@cs.elte.hu
%
% This file uses the Cork (T1) encoding.
%
\message{Hungarian hyphenation patterns V. 4.05 <2004/03/01> gam}
